    "Html": "<p>I load a page via HtmlWeb.Load().</p>\r\n<p>Sometimes the loaded page contains a php page as a link which gets displayed as follows in my bowser:</p>\r\n<p>e.g. href=&quot;http://www.test.com/hello.php?option=bla?param=more&quot;</p>\r\n<p>But when I read in this page via AgilityPack's HtmlWeb.Load() method the HtmlDocumemt's text property (including the link) becomes:</p>\r\n<p>href=&quot;http://www.test.com/hello.php?amp;option=bla?amp;param=more&quot;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>so the &quot;?&quot; get exchanged by &quot;?amp;&quot; !</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>1.) How can I avoid this?</p>\r\n<p>2.) Are there more similar substitutions AgilityPack does when extracting the links, which I should know?</p>\r\n<p>3.) Why does Agility Pack do this?</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Regards R4DIUM</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
    "PostedDate": "2009-05-26T18:03:49.72-07:00",
    "UserRole": null,
    "MarkedAsAnswerDate": null
  },
  {
    "Id": "200432",
    "ThreadId": "57563",
    "Html": "<p>I believe it is a bug that was never patched (or hasn't been patched yet).</p>\r\n<p>In the HtmlDocument source file change the following line in the HtmlEncode method from:</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#008000;font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"color:#008000;font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"color:#2b91af;font-size:x-small\"></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p>Regex <span style=\"color:#000000;font-size:x-small\">rx = </span><span style=\"color:#0000ff;font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"color:#0000ff;font-size:x-small\">new</span></span><span style=\"color:#000000;font-size:x-small\"> </span><span style=\"color:#2b91af;font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"color:#2b91af;font-size:x-small\">Regex</span></span><span style=\"color:#000000;font-size:x-small\">(</span><span style=\"color:#a31515;font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"color:#a31515;font-size:x-small\">&quot;&amp;(?!(amp;)|(lt;)|(gt;)|(quot;))&quot;</span></span><span style=\"color:#000000;font-size:x-small\">, </span><span style=\"color:#2b91af;font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"color:#2b91af;font-size:x-small\">RegexOptions</span></span><span style=\"font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">.IgnoreCase);</span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#000000\">To</span></p>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>Regex <span style=\"color:#000000;font-size:x-small\">rx = </span><span style=\"color:#0000ff;font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"color:#0000ff;font-size:x-small\">new</span></span><span style=\"color:#000000;font-size:x-small\"> </span><span style=\"color:#2b91af;font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"color:#2b91af;font-size:x-small\">Regex</span></span><span style=\"color:#000000;font-size:x-small\">(</span><span style=\"color:#a31515;font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"color:#a31515;font-size:x-small\">@&quot;&amp;(?!([a-z]+)|(\\#[0-9]+)|(\\#(x|X)[0-9a-fA-F]+);)&quot;</span></span><span style=\"color:#000000;font-size:x-small\">, </span><span style=\"color:#2b91af;font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"color:#2b91af;font-size:x-small\">RegexOptions</span></span><span style=\"font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">.IgnoreCase);</span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">And it should resolve that issue.</span></span></p>\r\n</p>",
    "PostedDate": "2009-06-11T08:04:31.277-07:00",
    "UserRole": null,
    "MarkedAsAnswerDate": null
  },
